tables
user, expense, category, settings

-- user
id
username
password_hash
display_name
created_at
updated_at

-- category
id
parent_id
name
description

-- expense
id
user_id
transaction_time
amount
category_id
description
created_at
updated_at

-- settings
id
key
value
for_user_id
updated_by_user_id
updated_at


-- functionality
default admin user (id = 0), creds taken from environment variables
CRUD for users (admin only)
CRUD for categories (admin only)
CRUD for expenses (user can only manage their own expenses)
view expenses (user can view all expenses, with filtering by date range, category, amount range)
view categories (all users can view categories in a hierarchical structure)
user settings (each user can have their own settings stored in the settings table)
authentication (login/logout)
authorization (role-based access control: admin and regular user)
password hashing and salting for user passwords
data validation for all inputs
error handling and logging
pagination for viewing expenses
search functionality for expenses (by description)
export expenses to CSV
concurrency handling for multiple users accessing/modifying data simultaneously
